<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 17 Mar 2026 12:43:52 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>USP39 在稳定 PB2 和协调核糖核蛋白组装方面的双重作用驱动 H5 流感病毒复制和致病性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dual-roles-of-usp39-in-stabilizing-pb2-and-orchestrating-ribonucleoprotein-assembly-drive-h5-influenza-virus-replication-and-pathogenicity</link><description>杨等人。鉴定 USP39 是被 H5 AIV 劫持的去泛素酶。 USP39 催化去泛素化 PB2，以防止其降解并维持聚合酶活性。同时，它促进了RNP组装的PB2-PB1关联。这种双重功能机制促进病毒复制，增强致病性，是一个有前途的抗 H5 治疗靶点。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dual-roles-of-usp39-in-stabilizing-pb2-and-orchestrating-ribonucleoprotein-assembly-drive-h5-influenza-virus-replication-and-pathogenicity2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 17 Mar 2026 12:43:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/dual-roles-of-usp39-in-stabilizing-pb2-and-orchestrating-ribonucleoprotein-assembly-drive-h5-influenza-virus-replication-and-pathogenicity</guid></item><item><title>成年早期饮酒与中年认知能力下降有关——即使在长期戒酒之后</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/early-adult-drinking-linked-to-middle-age-cognitive-decline-even-after-extended-abstinence</link><description>众所周知，饮酒是一种古老的应对压力的方法。但最近由马萨诸塞大学阿默斯特分校领导的研究发现，当这种自我药疗从成年早期开始时，负面的认知影响就会在中年开始显现出来——即使是在长期完全禁欲之后。该研究是&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/early-adult-drinking-linked-to-middle-age-cognitive-decline-even-after-extended-abstinence2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 17 Mar 2026 12:28:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/early-adult-drinking-linked-to-middle-age-cognitive-decline-even-after-extended-abstinence</guid></item><item><title>高海拔基因突变可能逆转髓磷脂损伤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/high-altitude-gene-mutation-may-reverse-myelin-damage</link><des